        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 5:42PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 542 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Tioga Pass, or 16 miles west of June Lake. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Merced Lake High Sierra Camp, Sunrise High Sierra Camp, Tuolumne
Meadows, Merced Lake Ranger Station, Morraine Dome Campground,
Vogelsang High Sierra Camp, Tuolumne High Sierra Camp, Glen Aulin
High Sierra Camp, Little Yosemite Valley Ranger Station, Tuolumne
Meadows Visitor Center, Tenaya Lake, Tuolumne Meadows Campground, and
Little Yosemite Valley Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
